, nuts, warm spices, and real maple syrup. Naturally sweetened, easy to make, and perfect for Christmas mornings or everyday breakfasts.","datePublished":"2025-12-17T14:57:52+00:00","image":["https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-13-min-scaled.jpg","https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-13-min-500x500.jpg","https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-13-min-500x375.jpg","https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-13-min-480x270.jpg"],"recipeYield":["14","14 cups"],"prepTime":"PT5M","cookTime":"PT60M","totalTime":"PT65M","recipeIngredient":["10 cups Old Fashioned Rolled Oats","1 cup Almonds (whole or halved)","1 cup Pecans (whole or halved)","1 cup Walnuts (whole or halved)","3/4 cup Coconut Oil (melted)","1 cup Pure Maple Syrup","1  tsp Pure Vanilla Extract","1 tsp Cinnamon","1 tsp Ginger","1 tsp Clove","1 tsp Nutmeg"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Preheat oven to 300\u00b0F","name":"Preheat oven to 300\u00b0F","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the melted coconut oil, maple syrup and vanilla to a small bowl or 1qt measuring cup and stir to combine.","name":"Add the melted coconut oil, maple syrup and vanilla to a small bowl or 1qt measuring cup and stir to combine.","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add the oats, nuts and spices to a large bowl and stir to combine.","name":"Add the oats, nuts and spices to a large bowl and stir to combine.","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-2","image":"https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-1-min-scaled.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Pour the syrup mixture over the oats and mix to coat everything evenly.","name":"Pour the syrup mixture over the oats and mix to coat everything evenly.","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-3","image":"https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-3-min-scaled.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Spread evenly on parchment lined baking sheet. It will be very full!","name":"Spread evenly on parchment lined baking sheet. It will be very full!","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-4","image":"https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-4-min-scaled.jpg"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Bake for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes. Cool completely before serving.","name":"Bake for 1 hour, stirring after 30 minutes. Cool completely before serving.","url":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#wprm-recipe-85527-step-0-5"}],"recipeCategory":["Breakfast","Dessert","Snack"],"recipeCuisine":["American"],"keywords":"granola with nuts","@id":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#recipe","mainEntityOfPage":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#webpage","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://brasspine.com/homemade-granola/#richSnippet"}}]}</script>
