<a href="https://brasspine.com/wprm_print/maple-spiced-homemade-granola-with-nuts" style="color: #ffffff;background-color: #000000;border-color: #333333;border-radius: 3px;padding: 5px 8px;" class="wprm-recipe-print wprm-recipe-link wprm-print-recipe-shortcode wprm-block-text-normal wprm-recipe-print-inline-button wprm-recipe-link-inline-button wprm-color-accent" data-recipe-id="85527" data-template="" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-recipe-print-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" x="0px" y="0px" width="16px" height="16px" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><g ><path fill="#ffffff" d="M19,5.09V1c0-0.552-0.448-1-1-1H6C5.448,0,5,0.448,5,1v4.09C2.167,5.569,0,8.033,0,11v7c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h4v4c0,0.552,0.448,1,1,1h12c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-4h4c0.552,0,1-0.448,1-1v-7C24,8.033,21.833,5.569,19,5.09z M7,2h10v3H7V2z M17,22H7v-9h10V22z M18,10c-0.552,0-1-0.448-1-1c0-0.552,0.448-1,1-1s1,0.448,1,1C19,9.552,18.552,10,18,10z"/></g></svg></span> Print Recipe</a></div><span id="dpsp-post-content-markup" data-image-pin-it="true"></span>
<div class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained">
<p class="has-text-align-center" style="font-size:16px">This post may contain affiliate links, which means I&rsquo;ll receive a commission if you purchase through my links, at no extra cost to you. Please read&nbsp;<a href="https://brasspine.com/disclaimer/" data-type="page" data-id="82775">full disclosure</a> for more information. As an Amazon Associate, I earn from qualifying purchases.</p>



<p>This <strong>homemade granola</strong> is loaded with nuts, infused with warm holiday spices, and sweetened with real maple syrup&mdash;no refined sugar in sight. It&rsquo;s a cozy, crowd-pleasing granola that will satisfy even the pickiest relatives this Christmas.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="768" height="1024" src="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-768x1024.jpg" alt="homemade granola with nuts in bags with ribbon" class="wp-image-85512" srcset="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-225x300.jpg 225w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" data-pin-media="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-15-min.jpg"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Homemade Granola for Busy Holiday Mornings</h2>



<p>I love making homemade granola, especially around the holidays. It&rsquo;s one of the few ways I can get my kids to eat nuts without commentary, negotiations, or dramatic sighing. <strong>It&rsquo;s filling, practical, and actually keeps everyone full</strong> long enough to get out the door&mdash;or at least survive the morning chaos.</p>



<p><strong>This is my go-to when family is in town</strong> because it feeds a crowd and can be customized without extra effort. Serve it with yogurt, applesauce, or whatever milk happens to be in the fridge. Add fruit, chocolate chips, or nothing at all. It&rsquo;s forgiving, flexible, and not precious&mdash;exactly what breakfast should be.</p>



<p><strong>It also makes an easy homemade holiday gift.</strong> Spoon it into a mason jar or cellophane bag, tie it up with <a class="thirstylink" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" title="Green Velvet Ribbon" href="https://amzn.to/3YwxkCn" data-linkid="85531" data-shortcode="true">velvet ribbon</a>, and suddenly you look far more put together than you feel. This recipe never disappoints, so be prepared to hand out the recipe when people ask.</p>



<p>I make a big batch every December fully intending it to last through the season. It never does. And yes, I keep making it long after the decorations come down.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="768" height="1024" src="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-768x1024.jpg" alt="homemade granola with nuts" class="wp-image-85518" srcset="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-225x300.jpg 225w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" data-pin-media="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-11-min.jpg"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Ingredient Notes</h2>



<p><strong>Oats</strong><br>Use old-fashioned rolled oats for the best texture. Skip steel-cut oats and quick oats&mdash;this is granola, not oatmeal cosplay.</p>



<p><strong>Maple Syrup</strong><br>Real maple syrup is key here. It gives this granola a deep, caramel-like sweetness that refined sugar just can&rsquo;t touch. Honey works as a substitute if needed or preferred.</p>



<p><strong>Coconut Oil</strong><br>This adds richness and helps everything crisp up evenly. Bonus: it subtly enhances the flavor without overpowering the spices.</p>



<p><strong>Nuts</strong><br>This is a true granola with nuts. I use pecans, walnuts, and almonds, but cashews, hazelnuts, or pistachios are all fair game. Use what you love&mdash;or what you have lurking in the pantry.</p>



<p><strong>Spice Blend</strong><br>Warm, cozy, and very holiday-forward. This blend gives the granola its &ldquo;Christmas granola&rdquo; status, but you can tweak it to your taste or simplify it for everyday use.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Tools You Will Need</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Large and small mixing bowl</li>



<li>Sheet pan. This <a class="thirstylink" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" title="Nordic Ware Half Sheet Pan" href="https://amzn.to/3so2GOY" data-linkid="80916" data-shortcode="true">Nordic Ware sheet pan</a> is my go-to.</li>



<li>Parchment paper</li>
</ul>



<p>(That&rsquo;s it. No special equipment, no nonsense.)</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="768" height="1024" src="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-768x1024.jpg" alt="homemade granola with nuts and cranberries" class="wp-image-85519" srcset="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-225x300.jpg 225w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" data-pin-media="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-8-min.jpg"></figure>


<div class="kb-row-layout-wrap kb-row-layout-id85511_2c1fe0-b9 alignnone wp-block-kadence-rowlayout"><div class="kt-row-column-wrap kt-has-1-columns kt-row-layout-equal kt-tab-layout-inherit kt-mobile-layout-row kt-row-valign-top">

<div class="wp-block-kadence-column kadence-column85511_1029b7-76 inner-column-1"><div class="kt-inside-inner-col">
<div class="wp-block-kadence-infobox kt-info-box85511_4baae2-35"><span class="kt-blocks-info-box-link-wrap info-box-link kt-blocks-info-box-media-align-top kt-info-halign-left"><div class="kt-infobox-textcontent"><h2 class="kt-blocks-info-box-title">Favorite Granola Add-Ins (After Baking)</h2></div></span></div>



<div class="wp-block-kadence-iconlist kt-svg-icon-list-items kt-svg-icon-list-items85511_10bf26-cd kt-svg-icon-list-columns-1 alignnone kt-list-icon-aligntop"><ul class="kt-svg-icon-list">
<li class="wp-block-kadence-listitem kt-svg-icon-list-item-wrap kt-svg-icon-list-item-85511_1a0de7-15 kt-svg-icon-list-style-default"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kt-svg-icon-list-single"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kt-svg-icon-list-text"><strong>Dried Cranberries:</strong> A little sweet and tart. These <a class="thirstylink" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" title="Dried Cranberries" href="https://amzn.to/4amWzhO" data-linkid="85533" data-shortcode="true">apple juice sweetened cranberries</a> are my favorite.</span></li>



<li class="wp-block-kadence-listitem kt-svg-icon-list-item-wrap kt-svg-icon-list-item-85511_4cf45b-f2 kt-svg-icon-list-style-default"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kt-svg-icon-list-single"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kt-svg-icon-list-text"><strong>Shredded Unsweetened Coconut:</strong> Adds great texture and a subtle coconut flavor that works with just about everything.</span></li>



<li class="wp-block-kadence-listitem kt-svg-icon-list-item-wrap kt-svg-icon-list-item-85511_860b4a-a1 kt-svg-icon-list-style-default"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kt-svg-icon-list-single"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kt-svg-icon-list-text"><strong>Raisins:</strong> Simple, classic, and reliably sweet&mdash;especially good if you&rsquo;re keeping things low effort.</span></li>



<li class="wp-block-kadence-listitem kt-svg-icon-list-item-wrap kt-svg-icon-list-item-85511_c74b35-88 kt-svg-icon-list-style-default"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kt-svg-icon-list-single"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kt-svg-icon-list-text"><strong>Chocolate Chips:</strong> For when you&rsquo;re feeling generous (or tired). The kids love them, and honestly, so do I.</span></li>



<li class="wp-block-kadence-listitem kt-svg-icon-list-item-wrap kt-svg-icon-list-item-85511_f3abb2-e1 kt-svg-icon-list-style-default"><span class="kb-svg-icon-wrap kb-svg-icon-fas_check-circle kt-svg-icon-list-single"><svg viewbox="0 0 512 512" fill="currentColor" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M504 256c0 136.967-111.033 248-248 248S8 392.967 8 256 119.033 8 256 8s248 111.033 248 248zM227.314 387.314l184-184c6.248-6.248 6.248-16.379 0-22.627l-22.627-22.627c-6.248-6.249-16.379-6.249-22.628 0L216 308.118l-70.059-70.059c-6.248-6.248-16.379-6.248-22.628 0l-22.627 22.627c-6.248 6.248-6.248 16.379 0 22.627l104 104c6.249 6.249 16.379 6.249 22.628.001z"></path></svg></span><span class="kt-svg-icon-list-text"><strong>Dried Banana Chips:</strong> Perfect paired with chocolate chips and great for adding crunch and a little extra sweetness.</span></li>
</ul></div>
</div></div>

</div></div>


<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Storing Granola</h2>



<p>Store your homemade granola in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 weeks&mdash;if it lasts that long. For gifting, mason jars or cellophane bags tied with <a class="thirstylink" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank" title="Green Velvet Ribbon" href="https://amzn.to/3YwxkCn" data-linkid="85531" data-shortcode="true">ribbon</a> work beautifully and keep the granola fresh and crunchy.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="768" height="1024" src="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-768x1024.jpg" alt="homemade granola with nuts in bags with ribbon" class="wp-image-85520" srcset="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-225x300.jpg 225w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" data-pin-media="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-19-min.jpg"></figure>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">What to Pair with Homemade Granola</h2>



<p><strong>Greek Yogurt + Fruit</strong> &ndash; Fresh or dried, a filling, fuss-free breakfast.</p>



<p><strong>Milk</strong> &ndash; Classic and simple, dairy or non-dairy.</p>



<p><strong>Baked Apples or Pears</strong> &ndash; Warm, cozy, and effortlessly impressive.</p>



<p><strong>Applesauce</strong> &ndash; Dairy-free, kid-friendly, and surprisingly genius.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading">Substitutions &amp; Variations</h2>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Nut-free:</strong> Swap the nuts for pumpkin seed or sunflower seeds.</li>



<li><strong>Honey:</strong> Swap the maple syrup for honey. I recommend adding a 1/4 cup of hot water to help thin the honey a bit so it&rsquo;s easier to mix in.</li>



<li><strong>Everyday version:</strong> Skip some of the holiday spices and add cinnamon only for an all-season granola.</li>



<li><strong>Extra crunch:</strong> Add sesame seeds or flax seeds for more texture and nutrition.</li>
</ul>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="768" height="1024" src="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-768x1024.jpg" alt="homemade granola with nuts " class="wp-image-85521" srcset="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-225x300.jpg 225w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-1536x2048.jpg 1536w, https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min-scaled.jpg 1920w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px" data-pin-media="https://brasspine.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Holiday-Spiced-Granola-14-min.jpg"></figure>



<p>Whether you&rsquo;re feeding a crowd, stocking the pantry, or gifting jars to unsuspecting relatives, this homemade Christmas granola is a winner. Simple, cozy, and lightly sweet, it&rsquo;s the kind of breakfast that makes mornings feel&hellip;almost civilized.</p>



<p>Happy Baking!</p>



<p>&hearts; Jessica</p>


